			<p align="justify">I'm currently merging the RPGDX users into the forum users table. This takes a bit more time than previous changes I made to RPGDX because the forums need a unique email and username, while RPGDX didn't even need a user name when it was first set up (let alone a unique one). I'm filling in [username]@please.correct.email where email problems occur and on double users I'll try to make best judgement by looking into their profile.</p>

			<p align="justify">Because RPGDX will be a bit of a mess when viewed halfway the process, I've put up this replacement index page. You can still visit the <a href="http://indie-rpg.net/indierpgforum/viewforum.php?f=1">forums</a> as usual.</p>

			<p align="justify">This move should be ok, I'm not removing anything from the database, only adding forum users and changing IDs. It should also not take longer than an hour, if it does you can assume that I'm having some very annoying problems...</p>

			<p align="justify">Thank you for your patience,<br />Bjørn Lindeijer</p>

